'''Alejandro''' "'''Álex'''" '''Baena Rodríguez''' (born 20 July 2001) is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left midfielder]] or [[attacking midfielder]] for [[La Liga]] club [[Atlético Madrid]] and the [[Spain national football team|Spain national team]].

==Club career==
===Villarreal===
Baena was born in [[Roquetas de Mar]], [[Province of Almería|Almería]], [[Andalusia]],<ref name="place"/> and joined [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]]'s youth setup in 2011, from [[CD Roquetas|Roquetas]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.elperiodicomediterraneo.com/noticias/deportes/alex-baena-perla-brilla-filial_1248357.html |title=Álex Baena, la 'perla' que brilla en el filial |trans-title=Álex Baena, the 'pearl' who shines in the reserves |newspaper=El Periódico Mediterráneo |language=es |date=3 October 2019 |accessdate=13 July 2020 |archive-date=2 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201102221611/https://www.elperiodicomediterraneo.com/noticias/deportes/alex-baena-perla-brilla-filial_1248357.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.roquetasdemar.es/noticias/contenido/alex-baena-jugador-roquetero-del-villarreal-ha-sido-convocado-por-la-seleccion-espanola-sub16_3666 |title=Álex Baena, jugador roquetero del Villarreal, ha sido convocado por la selección española sub16 |trans-title=Álex Baena, Roquetas-born Villarreal player, was called up to the Spain national under-16 team |publisher=Roquetas de Mar |language=es |date=26 September 2016 |accessdate=13 July 2020 |archive-date=2 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201102233358/https://www.roquetasdemar.es/noticias/contenido/alex-baena-jugador-roquetero-del-villarreal-ha-sido-convocado-por-la-seleccion-espanola-sub16_3666 |url-status=live}}</ref> He made his senior debut with [[Villarreal CF C|the C-team]] on 21 December 2018, coming on as a second-half [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in a 2–0 [[Tercera División]] home victory against [[UD Rayo Ibense|Rayo Ibense]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://golsmedia.com/un-electrico-villarreal-c-congela-al-rayo-ibense/ |title=Un eléctrico Villarreal C congela al Rayo Ibense |trans-title=An electric Villarreal C freeze Rayo Ibense |website=Golsmedia |language=es |date=21 December 2018 |accessdate=13 July 2020 |archive-date=3 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200803014312/https://golsmedia.com/un-electrico-villarreal-c-congela-al-rayo-ibense/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

Ahead of the [[2019–20 Segunda División B|2019–20 season]], Baena was assigned to [[Villarreal CF B|the reserves]] in [[Segunda División B]], debuting as a starter on 14 September 2019 in a 3–0 victory against [[UE Llagostera|Llagostera]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://golsmedia.com/el-villarreal-cf-b-golea-en-llagostera-y-sigue-lider/ |title=El Villarreal CF B golea en Llagostera y sigue líder |trans-title=Villarreal CF B thrash in Llagostera and remain leader |website=Golsmedia |language=es |date=14 September 2019 |access-date=13 July 2020 |archive-date=18 July 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200718224442/https://golsmedia.com/el-villarreal-cf-b-golea-en-llagostera-y-sigue-lider/ |url-status=live}}</ref> On 13 July of the following year, he made his first-team league debut, replacing fellow youth graduate [[Manu Trigueros]] in a 1–2 home loss against [[Real Sociedad]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/primera-division/cronica/2020/07/13/5f0c96cc268e3ea64a8b4580.html |title=La Real Sociedad despierta a tiempo y se mete en la pelea por Europa |trans-title=Real Sociedad wake up right on time and get inside the fight for Europa |newspaper=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] |publisher=Unidad Editorial |language=es |date=13 July 2020 |accessdate=13 July 2020 |archive-date=14 July 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200714033935/https://www.marca.com/futbol/primera-division/cronica/2020/07/13/5f0c96cc268e3ea64a8b4580.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

Baena scored his first professional goal on 5 November 2020, netting his club's third in a 4–0 [[UEFA Europa League]] home routing of [[Maccabi Tel Aviv F.C.|Maccabi Tel Aviv]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2029758--villarreal-vs-m-tel-aviv/ |title=Villarreal 4–0 Maccabi Tel-Aviv |publisher=[[UEFA]] |date=5 November 2020 |access-date=28 December 2020 |archive-date=20 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210120035955/https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2029758--villarreal-vs-m-tel-aviv/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Seven days later, he renewed his contract until 2025.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://villarrealcf.es/en/news/item/29055-the-villarreal-of-the-future |title=The Villarreal of the future |publisher=Villarreal CF |date=12 November 2020 |access-date=28 December 2020 |archive-date=11 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210111102429/https://villarrealcf.es/en/news/item/29055-the-villarreal-of-the-future |url-status=live}}</ref> On 19 August 2021, Baena moved to [[Segunda División]] club [[Girona FC|Girona]] on a one-year loan.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://villarrealcf.es/en/news/item/31479-alex-baena-loaned-to-girona-fc |title=Álex Baena, loaned to Girona FC |publisher=Villarreal CF |date=19 August 2021 |accessdate=19 August 2021 |archive-date=14 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220814153722/https://villarrealcf.es/en/news/item/31479-alex-baena-loaned-to-girona-fc |url-status=dead}}</ref> On 26 August 2022, he and teammate [[Nicolas Jackson]] were fully promoted to the main squad.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://villarrealcf.es/en/news/item/35264-baena-and-jackson-officially-become-first-team-players |title=Baena and Jackson officially become first-team players |publisher=Villarreal CF |date=26 August 2022 |accessdate=26 August 2022 |archive-date=26 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220826220932/https://villarrealcf.es/en/news/item/35264-baena-and-jackson-officially-become-first-team-players |url-status=dead}}</ref> In the [[2023–24 La Liga|2023–24 season]], he became the top assist provider in La Liga with 14 assists.<ref name="auto1">{{Cite news |url=https://en.as.com/resultados/futbol/primera/2023_2024/ranking/jugadores/asistencias-de-gol/ |title=LaLiga EA Sports: Goal assist |newspaper=[[Diario AS]] |publisher=Prisa |date=27 May 2024 |access-date=30 May 2024}}</ref>

===Atlético Madrid===
On 2 July 2025, Baena joined [[Atlético Madrid]], signing a five-year-contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/welcome-baena |title=Welcome, Baena! |publisher=Atlético Madrid |date=2 July 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Baena represented Spain at [[Spain national under-16 football team|under-16]], [[Spain national under-17 football team|under-17]], [[Spain national under-18 football team|under-18]], [[Spain national under-19 football team|under-19]] and [[Spain national under-20 football team|under-20]] levels, appearing in the [[2018 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Estos son los 20 convocados para la Eurocopa Sub-17 |url=http://www.sefutbol.com/oficial-estos-son-20-convocados-eurocopa-sub-17 |publisher=[[Royal Spanish Football Federation]] |date=23 April 2018 |language=es |access-date=3 May 2018 |archive-date=26 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626193809/http://www.sefutbol.com/oficial-estos-son-20-convocados-eurocopa-sub-17 |url-status=dead}}</ref> He also called up to the [[Spain national under-21 football team|under-21]] team for the [[2023 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]] where Spain finished as runners-up.<ref>{{cite web |title=Convocatoria de España para el Europeo sub-21|trans-title=Spain's squad list for the Under-21 European Championship|language=es |url=https://es.uefa.com/under21/news/0282-1828b68060d5-d0b13ba8c701-1000--convocatoria-de-espana-para-el-europeo-sub-21/ |publisher=UEFA |date=14 June 2023}}</ref><ref name="U21">{{cite web |title=2023 Euro U21 final: England vs Spain|url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/match/2036152--england-vs-spain/|publisher=UEFA|date=8 July 2023}}</ref>

In August 2023, Baena received his first call-up to the [[Spain national football team|Spain senior national team]] by head coach [[Luis de la Fuente (footballer, born 1961)|Luis de la Fuente]], for two [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying Group A|UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying]] matches against [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]] and [[Cyprus national football team|Cyprus]].<ref>{{cite web |date=1 September 2023 |title=Lista de convocados para los partidos contra Georgia y Chipre |trans-title=Squad list for matches against Georgia and Cyprus |url=https://rfef.es/es/noticias/oficial-lista-de-convocados-para-los-partidos-contra-georgia-y-chipre |access-date=2 September 2023 |publisher=[[Royal Spanish Football Federation]] |language=es}}</ref> He went on to score his first goal for Spain on his debut against the latter opponent in a 6–0 victory.<ref>{{Cite news |first=Javier |last=Mata |title=Baena marcó en su debut con la Selección, como Mario Gaspar y Pau Torres |url=https://as.com/futbol/primera/baena-marco-en-su-debut-con-la-seleccion-como-mario-gaspar-y-pau-torres-n/ |newspaper=[[Diario AS]] |publisher=Prisa |date=13 September 2023 |access-date=6 June 2025 |language=es}}</ref> In May 2024, Baena was named in the 26-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{Cite web |first=Tom |last=Hindle |title=Spain Euro 2024 squad: Who has Luis de la Fuente decided to take to Germany? |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/spain-euro-2024-squad-luis-de-la-fuente-germany/blte51a8d1b060b275a |website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]] |date=7 June 2024 |access-date=6 June 2025 |language=es}}</ref>

In July 2024, Baena was included in the [[Spain national under-23 football team|Spain U23]] squad for the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2024 Summer Olympics]] in Paris.<ref>{{cite web|title=Santi Denia da la lista con los 18 futbolistas para París 2024 y deja como suplentes a Iturbe, Juanlu, Mosquera y Camello|trans-title=Santi Denia announces the list of 18 players for Paris 2024 and leaves Iturbe, Juanlu, Mosquera and Camello as substitutes|language=es|url=https://www.rtve.es/deportes/20240710/juegos-olimpicos-paris-2024-lista-definitiva-espana-futbol/16181491.shtml|publisher=RTVE|date=10 July 2024}}</ref> He scored a goal from a free kick in the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament final|gold medal]] match against France,<ref>{{cite web |title=Álex Baena, ¡oro olímpico!|trans-title=Álex Baena, Olympic gold!|language=es|url=https://cadenaser.com/andalucia/2024/08/09/alex-baena-oro-olimpico-ser-almeria-2|first=Rafa|last=Góngora|publisher=Cadena SER|date=9 August 2024}}</ref> where Spain won by 5–3 [[Overtime (sports)#Association football|after extra time]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Spain win gold in Olympic final for the ages |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/olympicgames/paris2024/mens/articles/match-report-gold-medal-france-spain |publisher=FIFA|date=9 August 2024}}</ref>

